perms.permsHelp:
Assigns permissions to a role.

Examples:
`{{prefix}}perms add everyone music.*` - Give everyone music permissions
`{{prefix}}perms deny Moderators misc.cat` - Dont allow the `Moderators` role to use the cat command
`{{prefix}}perms deny luke misc.doge` - Dont allow the user `luke` to use the doge command
`{{prefix}}perms list Moderators` - List the permissions for the `Moderators` role
`{{prefix}}perms remove everyone music.*` - Remove the music permissions from everyone
`{{prefix}}perms clear Moderators` - Clear the permissions for the `Moderators` role

For a list of permissions, see {{prefix}}perms nodes
perms.permsNodesDescription: Add `-` in front of a permission to deny it from a user.

admin.roleHelp:
Manage Roles

Examples:
`{{prefix}}role add Moderators Admins` - Add the `Admins` role to everyone with the `Moderators` role
`{{prefix}}role add luke Admins` - Add the user `luke` to the role `Admins`
`{{prefix}}role remove everyone Moderators` - Remove the `Moderators` role from everyone

admin.cleanHelp:

Examples:
`{{prefix}}clean` - Cleans 10 messages
`{{prefix}}clean 100` - Cleans 100 messages
`{{prefix}}clean 100 luke` - Cleans 100 messages from the user `luke`

settings.greetingHelp:
Sets a welcome message for the server.

Examples:
`{{prefix}}greeting #general Welcome %mention% to %server%!` - Sends `Welcome @luke to <your server name>!` to #general when luke joins your server.
`{{prefix}}greeting dm Welcome %username%!` - Welcomes a user to your server in direct messages.
`{{prefix}}greeting disable` - Disables the greeting.
settings.farewellHelp:
Sets a message for when a user leaves the server.

Examples:
`{{prefix}}farewell #general %username% left %server%... bye bye %username%...` - Sends `luke left <your server>... bye bye luke..` to #general when luke leaves your server.
`{{prefix}}farewell` - Disables the farewell
settings.farewellTextUndefined: You haven't specified a farewell message!
settings.prefixHelp:
Sets the command prefix.

Examples:
`{{prefix}}prefix !` - Sets the prefix to `!`
`{{prefix}}prefix disable` - Disables the custom command prefix.
settings.prefixDisable: Successfully disabled the prefix. All commands should now be used like: `{{prefix}}ping`
settings.prefixSet: Successfully set the prefix. All commands should now be used like: `{{prefix}}ping`
settings.logHelp: Sets a log channel for joins and leaves.
settings.accessroleHelp: Sets a role that people have to have to use the bot. Use `{{prefix}}accessrole disable` to disable
settings.localeHelp: Sets a locale. See `{{prefix}}locale list` for a list of locales.
settings.userlocaleHelp: Sets the locale for the user. See `{{prefix}}userlocale list` for a list of locales.
autorole.autoroleHelp:
Assigns roles.

Examples:
`{{prefix}}autorole add join Humans` - Gives the role `Humans` to users on join.
`{{prefix}}autorole add get Announcements` - Users can now do `{{prefix}}getrole Announcements` to get that role.
`{{prefix}}autorole add bot Bots` - Bots will get this role when they join.
`{{prefix}}autorole remove join Humans` - Remove the autorole for `Humans`.
`{{prefix}}autorole list` - List all autoroles.

Ensure the role for me is above the role you want me to give, otherwise I wont have permission.
autorole.getroleHelp: Gets a role with the `get` condition from {{prefix}}autorole
autorole.getroleNoConditon: This role doesn't have the `get` condition, the owner can add it by doing `{{prefix}}autorole add get {{role}}`.
autorole.autoroleNoPermission: You cannot manage roles above yours.

music.playHelp:
Plays a song.

Examples:
`{{prefix}}play Whatever you write here will search youtube`
`{{prefix}}play https://soundcloud.com/sonevable/gin-wigmore-written-in-the-water-nev-edit`
`{{prefix}}play https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v372aagNItc`

A range of sites are supported.

`{{prefix}}repeat all` - Repeat the whole queue.

music.autoplayHelp:
Sets a song or playlist or livestream to play while the queue is empty.

Examples:
`{{prefix}}autoplay https://twitch.tv/monstercat` - Plays monstercat while the queue is empty.
`{{prefix}}autoplay disable` - Disables autoplay
